---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'There are a lot of agencies out there. What makes Obvius Digital different?',
    answer: 'Most "top-rated agencies" focus on vanity metrics like "impressions." We focus on the "Request Proposal" button. We specialize in performance-based solutions specifically for independent SMBs. We prioritize transparency and data. As our clients have noted: "They were the first agency that explained the \'why\' behind the SEO, not just the \'what\'."',
  },
  {
    question: 'How involved do I need to be in the digital marketing process?',
    answer: 'We know you\'re busy running a business, so we handle the heavy lifting while keeping you in the loop. Whether you need performance-based digital marketing solutions in Toronto or a full brand refresh, we act as an extension of your team. You\'ll always have a direct line to the experts who are actually doing the work. No "account managers" or layers of bureaucracy.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you meet in person for GTA-based clients?',
    answer: 'Absolutely. While we serve clients throughout Ontario, we believe there is immense value in local partnership. As a Toronto-based agency specializing in social media marketing, SEO, and web design, we are happy to meet at your office or a local coffee shop in the Greater Toronto Area to discuss your goals in person.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do you actually get my business to show up on the first page of Google?',
    answer: 'It\'s a mix of technical SEO, local authority building, and modern AI tools. We don\'t just "guess"; we analyze your Toronto competitors to see exactly where they are vulnerable. One of our partners saw a 40% jump in local leads by focusing on the "near me" searches we identified during their initial audit.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When will I see my business start to climb in search rankings?',
    answer: 'While we are considered one of the top-rated digital marketing agencies in Toronto, we don\'t believe in over-promising. SEO is a marathon, but we aim for "sprints" of success. Most clients see significant movement in search rankings within 3 to 6 months. We focus on quick wins first—like Google Business Profile optimization—to get the phones ringing while the long-term SEO takes root.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How is Obvius Digital using digital marketing with AI to improve my results?',
    answer: 'We use AI to bring a new level of creativity and security to your brand. We use it to instantly turn verbal concepts into stunning visual prototypes, allowing you to "see" our ideas before we build them. Furthermore, we use AI-driven protocols to proofread and double-check every line of code and copy, giving you the security of knowing your project is polished and error-free.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you handle my social media, or just the technical side of the website?',
    answer: 'We are among the Toronto-based agencies specializing in social media marketing and holistic content strategy. We ensure your brand voice is consistent across social media and your website, creating a seamless "loop" that keeps local customers engaged with your business.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What does a typical project cost with a Toronto-based agency like Obvius Digital?',
    answer: 'Typical average costs for SEO services from Toronto agencies can range from $1,500 to $10k+ depending on the complexity. However, we focus on the "sweet spot" for SMBs. By staying lean and local, we provide high-end, performance-based digital marketing solutions in Toronto at a price point that makes sense for an independent business\'s bottom line.',
  },
];
---

<section class="faq section">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <span class="section-label">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Common Questions</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--color-grey-dark); margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1rem;">
      Everything you want to know about working with Obvius Digital.
    </p>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item" id={`faq-${i + 1}`}>
          <summary>{faq.question}</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__body">
            <p>{faq.answer}</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
